South African President, Cyril Ramaphosa, will address the nation on the outcomes of the special cabinet meeting on the coronavirus outbreak this evening. The number of people diagnosed with the coronavirus in SA has increased to 51. The health department announced an increase of 13 patients on Sunday morning — from  38 cases recorded on Saturday. The health ministry announced that seven of the new cases were in Gauteng, five in the Western Cape and one in KwaZulu-Natal.